        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_æmbærzyn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>æmbærzyn</orth><form type="participle"
                            ><orth>æmbærzt</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>æmbærzun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth>æmbarzt</orth></form></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>покрывать</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>cover</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>xæxtyl zymæg jæ ūrs kærc æræmbærzta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>зима накрыла горы своей белой шубой</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the winter covered the mountains with its white fur coat</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>28</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>arf wærm yskʼaxtoj æmæ jæ wælijæ kærdæǵytæj bambærztoj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>вырыли глубокую яму и сверху покрыли ее травой</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>dug a deep hole and covered it with grass</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>26</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>bambærzta jyl nymæt</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>covered her with burka</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q/>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>72</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>lægæt ærcaræzta, zæxxæj jæ bambærzta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>устроила берлогу, покрыла ее землей</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>(she) made a den, covered it with sod</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Æfx._Xæs."
                            /><biblScope>99</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>Xadizæt Kalaxanbæl iskodta ors zældagæ pʼolci, ba-ʽj-æmbarzta saw
                            xizæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Хадизат надела на Калахан белое шелковое платье, накрыла ее черным
                                кружевным платком</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Khadizat put on a white silk dress on Kalahan, covered her with a
                                black lace shawl</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1949 II
                            46</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>agæ fæjnægæj æmbærzuni ǧud kæntæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>позаботьтесь, чтобы накрыть котел доской</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>make sure to cover the boiler with a plank</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."
                            /><biblScope>33%l12%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Сращение преверба <ref type="xr"/> (← %iam-%i) с глагольной
                    основой %i*barg-%i, *barz- (и.е. %i*bherǵh-%i: <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Pokorny"/><biblScope>146</biblScope></bibl>), являющейся
                    общим скифо-славяно-балто-германским достоянием. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>bregǫ</w>
                        <gloss><q>берегу</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>берегу</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>birg-</w>
                        <gloss><q>беречь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>bergen</w>
                        <gloss><q>прятать</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр. Может быть, сюда же
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>barəg-</w>
                        <gloss><q>принимать к себе</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*ambarzy(ʼmβrz-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>прием</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ср. также <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_nyværzæn"/> ‘изголовье’, д. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_iværzun"/> ‘обещать’, и, может быть, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æmbæxsyn"/>.%n<bibl><author>Bailey</author><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_JRAS"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1954, стр.
                            30</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Fusion of the preverb <ref type="xr"/> (← %iam-%i) with the verb
                    stem %i*barg-%i, *barz- (Indo-European %i*bherǵh-%i: <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Pokorny"/><biblScope>146</biblScope></bibl>), which is a
                    common Scythian-Slavic-Baltic-German heritage. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>bregǫ</w>
                        <gloss><q>(I) take care</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>beregu</w>
                        <gloss><q>(I) take care</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>birg-</w>
                        <gloss><q>take care</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>bergen</w>
                        <gloss><q>hide (smth.)</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. Probably, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>barəg-</w>
                        <gloss><q>take (smb.) in</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*ambarzy(ʼmβrz-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>reception</q></gloss></mentioned>. See also <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_nyværzæn"/> ‘bedhead’, Digor <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_iværzun"/> ‘promise’, and, probably, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æmbæxsyn"/>.%n<bibl><author>Bailey</author><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_JRAS"/><biblScope xml:lang="en">1954, p.
                    30</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
